{{Transcript|event}}
{{Transcript list|Easter Bunny|Chocolate demon}}

==Starting off==
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Hello? Can you hear me? I need help!
* '''Player:''' Hello? This is [player] here. What's going on?
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' This is the Easter Bunny. I'm stuck in my office, and I'm having to use my emergency broadcast system to talk to you.
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' We're having some sort of infestation down here. The chocolate's gone mad! Please come down to my office and help me. There's a reward.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Is it safe for me?}}
** '''Player:''' Is it safe for me?
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' I expect so. Just... don't eat the chocolate. Can you come to my office now, please?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Sure, I'll come down to your office.}}
** '''Player:''' Sure, I'll come down to your office.
** {{qact|The player enters the warrens, and is approached by a chocolate chicken and chocolate bunny.}}
** '''Chocolate chicken:''' {{overhead|Grrr!}}
** '''Player:''' Um... what are those things? Get away from me!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Nope, I'm not interested.}}
** {{tmissing}}

===Trying to enter the storerooms===
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' The storeroom's full of the dratted critters! Fortunately I don't need anything from there just now, so you can leave them alone.
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' My office is at the eastern side of the warren. Please come and help me.
* {{tact|end}}

===Getting attacked by the chocolate creatures===
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
** {{overhead|Graarh!}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
** {{overhead|Kkrrrr!}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 3}}
** {{overhead|Hiss!}}

===Listening to the speakers===
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' My office is at the eastern side of the warren. Please come and help me.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny in his office===
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Ah, [player], thank you so much for coming to help me. It's terrible, simply terrible. I can't understand it at all.
* '''Player:''' What are you talking about?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' My job's supposed to be simple - I get chocolate eggs from the bird and tell the rabbits to deliver them in the springtime. That's all I should have to do!
* '''Player:''' Focus! What's been happening here?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' It's the eggs, the chocolate eggs for Easter. They've been hatching. Now my warren's infested by demonic chocolate critters. They're terrifying!
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What could have made the eggs start hatching?}}
** '''Player:''' What could have made the eggs start hatching?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I've no idea. The bird doesn't know either. I suspect magical sabotage. Maybe someone really hates Easter eggs.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|How do I get rid of the creatures?}}
** '''Player:''' How do I get rid of the creatures?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I have a plan! Last Halloween, that Diango fellow sold me a 'Phantasmic Destabliser Mark 500'. He said they were brilliant, and he only wanted 1,000,000 coins.
** {{tcond|If the player completed the 2013 Halloween event:}}
*** '''Player:''' You paid Diango 1,000,000 coins for a ghost buster? He was just handing them out last year. I had one.
*** '''Easter Bunny:''' Oh... drat. Maybe I should just use the Grand Exchange.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tcond|If the player didn't complete the 2013 Halloween event:}}
*** '''Easter Bunny:''' It's a sort of weapon. I gather Diango originally had it built to attack some ghosts.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Anyway, this blaster might be just what we need. If we load it with different ammunition, it should work on chocolate instead of ghosts.
** '''Player:''' So where is the blaster, and what ammunition are we going to use on it?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' It's in a crate in the bird's room, at the north end of my warren. I'll use the loudspeakers to give more instructions when you've found it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'm not interested.}}
** {{tmissing}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny again===
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Have you found the blaster yet? It's in a crate in the bird's room, at the north end of my warren.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Remind me what I'm supposed to be doing.}}
** '''Player:''' Remind me what I'm supposed to be doing.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Go to the bird's room, at the north of my warren. In a crate, you'll find a weapon that we can adapt to work on the creatures.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I'll use the loudspeakers to give more instructions when you've found it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll be back.}}
** {{tmissing}}

==Off to the bird's room==
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Have you found the blaster yet? It's in a crate in the bird's room, at the north end of my warren.
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the crate===
* {{tbox|pic=Empty blaster detail.png|pic2=Bronze pickaxe detail.png|You find a blaster and a pickaxe.}}
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Great! Now, there are some rocks in the middle of my warren containing an explosive mineral. Mine some, and load the blaster.
* {{tact|end}}

====Trying to fire the unloaded blaster====
* {{mes|The blaster doesn't have any suitable ammunition for that.}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny after finding the blaster===
* {{tmissing}}

===Entering the room with the minerals===
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' The rocks containing explosive minerals are in the middle of my warren, near the entrance. Mine some, and load it into the blaster.
* {{tact|end}}

====Mining the minerals====
* {{mes|You swing your pick at the rock.}}
* {{mes|You manage to mine some of the mineral.}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny after loading the blaster with minerals===
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Have you loaded the blaster with the oil yet?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Remind me what I'm supposed to be doing.}}
** '''Player:''' Remind me what I'm supposed to be doing.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Near the mining rocks, there's a gungy pool where a flammable oil floats to the surface. Try to suck some up the blaster's nozzle.
** '''Player:''' I'll be back.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll be back.}}
** {{tact|above}}

===Loading the blaster===
* {{tbox|pic=Incomplete blaster detail.png|You load the blaster with explosive rounds.}}
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Excellent! Now you need some flammable oil. There's a gungy pool near the mining rocks with an oily scum on the surface.
* {{tact|end}}

===Filling the blaster with oil===
* {{tbox|pic=Easter blaster detail.png|Some oil has oozed up to the surface from the rotting vegetation in the pool's depths. You suck some of it into the blaster.}}
* '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' That's the weapon all prepared. Now you can use it to wipe out those horrible critters.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny after filling the blaster with oil===
* {{tmissing}}

====Chocolate creature upon death====
* {{overhead|*glub glub glub*}}

====Trying to shoot the blaster while too close to a wall====
* {{mes|You might get hurt if you shoot the wall at short range!}}

====Trying to shoot the blaster outside the warren====
* {{mes|This blaster is for use on the chocolate critters infesting the Easter Bunny's warren.}}

====Trying to shoot the blaster in the Easter Bunny's office====
* {{mes|The Easter Bunny is unlikely to appreciate you doing that in here.}}

===Chocolate creature massacre===
* {{tcond|After killing 1 creature:}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Excellent! 4 more left to kill.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|After killing 2 creatures:}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' You're doing great. Three more to go.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|After killing 3 creatures:}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Excellent! 2 more left to kill.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|After killing 4 creatures:}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Just one left now.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|After killing 5 creatures:}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' Well done - you've got them all!
** {{qact|The chocolate demon reveals itself.}}
** '''Chocolate demon:''' Graaaah! How dare you slay my creatures? But I shall not fail my master.
** '''Player:''' Your creatures? You mean you made those chocolate things come out of the eggs?
** '''Chocolate demon:''' My master summoned me to end this Easter foolishness. Humans seize any excuse to pretend a season is special, with frivolous gifts and unhealthy foodstuffs.
** '''Player:''' Who is your master?
** '''Chocolate demon:''' He calls himself Anti-Santa. Normally he focuses on destroying Christmas, but he gets very bored in the springtime, so he's branching out.
** {{tcond|If the player participated in the 2014 Christmas event:}}
*** '''Player:''' Oh, him. Yes, I met Anti-Santa last Christmas. So he summoned a chocolate demon to attack Easter?
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tcond|If the player didn't participate in the 2014 Christmas event:}}
*** '''Player:''' So this Anti-Santa person summoned a chocolate demon to attack Easter?
*** {{tact|continues}}
** '''Chocolate demon:''' My chocolatey powers make me the ideal agent to attack the Easter Bunny's chocolate eggs.
** '''Chocolate demon:''' With no chocolate eggs, there can be no celebration. And the eggs were easy to sabotage - it took very little of my magic to animate and possess them.
** '''Player:''' Are you going to give up now?
** '''Chocolate demon:''' No! You have slain my creatures, but I still have my magic. As long as I live, there will be no Easter festivity here!
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' He's made of chocolate. That means you can destroy him with the blaster. Quick - save Easter!
** {{tact|end}}

===Slaying the chocolate demon===
* {{tcond|Upon killing the chocolate demon:}}
** '''Chocolate demon:''' {{overhead|Aaarrgh!}}
** '''Easter Bunny (speaker):''' It's dead! You've saved Easter! Come back to my office - I've got a reward for you.
** {{tact|end}}

==Finishing up==
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Thank you so much for your help! Now those critters and the demon have gone, my rabbits can get back to work.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I'm gonna give you my spare boots. I think they'll suit you. I'll give you a couple Easter eggs too.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' If you'd like more Easter eggs, go up to my storeroom. It's still infested with the critters, but there are Easter eggs in there somewhere.
* {{tbox|pic=Bunny feet detail.png|The Easter Bunny awards you a pair of bunny feet boots.}}
* {{tact|end}}

